<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861205-0014 </DOCNO><HL> )HL    Who's News:Corning Glass NamesGardner ChairmanOf Its Steuben Unit</HL><DD> 12/05/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GLW WNEWS </IN><DATELINE> CORNING, N.Y.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Corning Glass Works named Kirtland C. Gardner III, formerly president of its Steuben Glass unit, to succeed Amory Houghton Jr. as chairman of Steuben.    Mr. Gardner, 52 years old, also was named to the newly created position of vice president, external affairs, for Corning, a glass, optics and housewares company.    Mr. Houghton, 60, resigned the post at Steuben, a maker of art glass and giftware, upon his election last month to the U.S. House of Representatives. He also stepped down as a Corning director and as chairman of the company's executive committee.    The new president of Steuben is Susan B. King, 46, formerly Corning's vice president and director of corporate communications and consumer affairs.    David N. Van Allen, formerly vice president, corporate planning services, was named to succeed Ms. King. Robert Barker, provost of Cornell University, was named a director. </TEXT></DOC>